properties.Name: InsuranceRestrictionType
properties.Description:
A restriction or requirement placed upon the use, procurement or sale of the associated Insurance Product.

Most insurance companies have required minimum amounts of coverage on associated types of insurance.  

Ex:
- Insured must have at least $250,000 of protection on auto policy or $300,000 of protection on your homeowner's policy
- May not be sold to those under 21
- May only be sold to state employees
